---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import H1 from "../components/type/H1.astro";
import H2 from "../components/type/H2.astro";
import Lead from "../components/type/Lead.astro";
import CTA from "../components/CTA.astro";
const call_url = "https://calendly.com/django-belcoda/30min";
const documentation_url =
  "https://belcoda.notion.site/Documentation-835d2aed77ea4206ba97f6f71b962509?pvs=4";
---

<Layout title="Privacy - Belcoda">
  <main>
    <section class="container mx-auto px-8 py-20">
      <H1>Privacy Policy</H1>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <Lead>
          <span class="font-extrabold"
            >Belcoda LLC takes privacy seriously.</span
          > To better protect your privacy we provide this privacy policy notice
          explaining the way your personal information is collected and used.</Lead
        >
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <H2>Collection of Routine Information</H2>

        <p>
          The Belcoda application, this website, and other Belcoda products
          track basic information about their visitors and users. This
          information includes, but is not limited to, IP addresses, browser
          details, timestamps and referring pages. None of this information can
          personally identify specific visitors or users. The information is
          tracked for routine administration and maintenance purposes.
        </p>

        <H2>Collection of Personal Information</H2>

        <p>
          As part of the necessary operations of Belcoda products, this website,
          and the Belcoda application, certain personal information is
          collected. This information includes, but is not limited to, email
          addresses, phone numbers, and names. This information is used to
          create user accounts, send notifications, and provide customer
          support. This information is stored securely and is not shared with
          third parties.
        </p>

        <p>
          Self hosted instances of the Belcoda application do not transmit
          personal information to Belcoda LLC. The personal information
          collected via self hosted instances of the Belcoda application is
          stored on the instance manager's infrastructure and is not accessible
          by Belcoda LLC.
        </p>

        <p>
          Depending on its configuration settings, a self-hosted Belcoda
          instance may transmit routine information to Belcoda LLC. This
          information includes, but is not limited to, IP addresses, browser
          details, timestamps and referring pages. None of this information can
          personally identify specific visitors or users. The information is
          tracked for routine administration and maintenance purposes.
        </p>

        <H2>Cookies</H2>
        <p>
          Where necessary, this website, and other Belcoda products, use cookies
          to store information about a visitorâ€™s preferences and history in
          order to better serve the vistor or user and/or present the visitor or
          user with customized content.
        </p>

        <H2>Advertisement and Other Third Parties</H2>
        <p>
          Belcoda does not user advertising or third party trackers, and does
          not share any user information with third parties, other than for the
          purposes of administering the Belcoda application and related
          products.
        </p>

        <H2>Links to Third Party Websites</H2>
        <p>
          We have included links on this website, and in other Belcoda products,
          for your use and reference. We are not responsible for the privacy
          policies on these websites. You should be aware that the privacy
          policies of these websites may differ from our own.
        </p>

        <H2>Security</H2>
        <p>
          The security of your personal information is important to us, but
          remember that no method of transmission over the Internet, or method
          of electronic storage, is 100% secure. While we strive to use
          commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we
          cannot guarantee its absolute security.
        </p>

        <H2>Changes To This Privacy Policy</H2>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy is effective as of 6 June 2024 and will remain in
          effect except with respect to any changes in its provisions in the
          future, which will be in effect immediately after being posted on this
          page.
        </p>

        <p>
          we reserve the right to update or change our Privacy Policy at any
          time and you should check this Privacy Policy periodically. If we make
          any material changes to this Privacy Policy, we will notify you either
          through the email address you have provided us, or by placing a
          prominent notice on our website.
        </p>

        <H2>Contact Information</H2>
        <p>
          For any questions or concerns regarding the privacy policy, please
          send us an email to <a href="mailto:privacy@belcoda.org"
            >hello@belcoda.org</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <CTA call_url={call_url} get_started_url={documentation_url} />
    <Footer call_url={call_url} documentation_url={documentation_url} />
  </main>

  <style>
    .astro-a {
      position: absolute;
      top: -32px;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translatex(-50%);
      width: 220px;
      height: auto;
      z-index: -1;
    }
    a {
      @apply font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500 hover:underline;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 4rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 1em;
    }
    .text-gradient {
      background-image: var(--accent-gradient);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-size: 400%;
      background-position: 0%;
    }
    .instructions {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent-light), 25%);
      background: linear-gradient(
        rgba(var(--accent-dark), 66%),
        rgba(var(--accent-dark), 33%)
      );
      padding: 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
    }
    .instructions code {
      font-size: 0.8em;
      font-weight: bold;
      background: rgba(var(--accent-light), 12%);
      color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 0.3em 0.4em;
    }
    .instructions strong {
      color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
    }
    .link-card-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(24ch, 1fr));
      gap: 2rem;
      padding: 0;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
